navy officials have recommended disciplinary 
action against only one officer of the uss vincennes in the downing 
of an iranian airliner july 3 the washington post reported in 
sundays editions 
the recommendation of the navy board resulted from statements 
following the panels review of a report scheduled to be presented 
to defense secretary frank carlucci this week 
the report places most of the blame on the aegis cruisers 
operations officer for his role in misinterpreting information 
which resulted in the ship mistakenly shooting down the airbus 
killing all 299 aboard the newspaper said 
the report currently being reviewed by marine gen william j 
crowe jr chairman of the joint chiefs of staff recommends a 
letter of reprimand to the officer to be included in his official 
file the officers name had not been released 
earlier versions of the document compiled by an investigative 
team headed by rear adm william n fogarty said human error was a 
major factor in the accident 
