in either of those bills hobbs said the presidents top 
advisors will recommend a veto if theres no work requirement 
the house conferees already have agreed to a senate provision 
also added under administration pressure requiring states to 
eventually enroll 22 percent of nonexempt welfare recipients in 
their jobs programs 
its unclear whether lawmakers when they return after labor 
day will resume discussions about dropping the twoparent 
provision or try to keep it and hammer out a compromise on the work 
requirement 
but clinton said the negotiators are so close to an overall 
agreement theres no way the whole thing could fall victim to a 
veto over this mandatory work issue 
well keep plugging away weve still got time he said 
