<TEXT>
broadcasters are being urged to restrict the 
airing of sexually explicit material while the federal 
communications commission studies new guidelines to shield children 
from indecent programs 
i would tell broadcasters they need to be cautious said 
jeff baumann general counsel for the national association of 
broadcasters 
the fcc is under orders from a federal appeals court to review 
the agencys rules governing sexually explicit material on 
nighttime television and radio the inquiry is due to begin shortly 
and take several months before new rules are adopted said diane 
killory fcc general counsel 
in the meantime it is unclear at what times in the evening 
indecent programs can be aired without fear that unsupervised 
children will be listening or watching 
the appeals court ruling suspended a 2000 fine the fcc levied 
early this year against kzkctv kansas city for airing the movie 
private lessons during prime time in may 1987 the action had 
been the first against a broadcaster since the fcc toughened its 
decency standards in april 1987 
the july 29 court decision could affect discussions by house and 
senate conferees who will consider an amendment to a budget bill 
sponsored by sen jesse helms rnc to prohibit stations from 
airing indecent material at any time 
congressional sources who spoke on condition of anonymity said 
despite indications the measure would be struck down in court 
chances were good that an electionyear congress would pass a ban 
on broadcast indecency 
courts have ruled that indecent but not obscene material is 
protected by the first amendment though childrens access to it 
may be regulated 
the july 29 ruling affirmed the fccs definition of indecency 
adopted from a supreme court ruling language that depicts or 
describes in terms patently offensive as measured by contemporary 
community standards for the broadcast medium sexual or excretory 
activities or organs 
obscenity is defined similarly except that it also appeals to 
the prurient interest and lacks serious scientific literary 
artistic or political value 
the threejudge panel had trouble with the fccs policy of 
restricting indecent programming to between midnight and 6 am 
the time the agency determined that children were not likely to be 
in the audience 
the court said the fcc had not adequately thought through 
the time restrictions and must try to devise a rule that will 
promote parental as distinguished from government control 
the court upheld an fcc warning issued against disc jockey 
howard stern for portions of his show that aired between 6 am and 
10 am the fcc reads that part of the decision to permit continued 
enforcement of its decency rules during the daytime killory said 
but after that it seems questionable whether the court would 
let us enforce the indecency rule during an evening broadcast until 
we have concluded our inquiry and set a specific time in the 
evening killory said 
the court didnt say when daytime ends or evening begins 
she said 
it is possible the fcc wont conclude the inquiry and approve 
new rules before the end of the year she said in that case the 
matter might be handled by a commission shaped by a new 
administration 
</TEXT>
